1
00:02:33,111 --> 00:02:34,112
[Man Screams]

2
00:02:35,864 --> 00:02:39,409
[Man Narrating] So where are you?
You're in some motel room.

3
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:42,912
You just-- You just wake up,
and you're in a motel room.

4
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:45,999
There's the key. It feels like maybe
it's the first time you've been there,

5
00:02:46,082 --> 00:02:50,670
but... perhaps you've
been there for a week,

6
00:02:50,753 --> 00:02:53,298
three months.

7
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:55,967
It's kind of hard to say.
I don't-- I don't know.

8
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:58,136
It's just an anonymous room.

9
00:02:58,219 --> 00:03:01,347
- [Radio Sportscast, Indistinct]
- This guy.

10
00:03:01,431 --> 00:03:04,434
He's here already.

11
00:03:04,517 --> 00:03:06,769
Lenny!

12
00:03:06,811 --> 00:03:10,940
It's Leonard...
Like I told you before.

13
00:03:11,024 --> 00:03:14,319
Did you?
I must have forgot.

14
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,946
I guess I've already
told you about my condition.

15
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:21,451
Oh, well, only every time I see you.
[Clicks Tongue]

16
00:03:28,249 --> 00:03:31,210
- My car.
- This is your car.

17
00:03:31,294 --> 00:03:34,297
Oh, you're in a playful mood.

18
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:36,215
It's not good for you to make
fun of someone's handicap.

19
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:39,302
- [Car Alarm Chirps]
- Just trying to have a little fun.

20
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:45,475
- [Engine Starts]
- [Radio Newscast, Indistinct]

21
00:03:45,516 --> 00:03:48,978
- Roll up your window.
- Hmm?

22
00:03:52,023 --> 00:03:54,317
It's broken.

23
00:03:54,359 --> 00:03:58,821
I can get that fixed for you.
So where to, Sherlock?

24
00:03:58,863 --> 00:04:01,824
- I got a lead on a place.
- Oh, what the hell do you
wanna go there for?

25
00:04:01,866 --> 00:04:05,078
- You know it?
- Yeah, it's just this
fucked-up building.

26
00:04:05,161 --> 00:04:09,499
- Why Do you wanna go there?
- Don't remember.

27
00:04:28,893 --> 00:04:31,020
Looks like somebody's home.

28
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:33,439
Ah, that thing's
been here for years.

29
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:35,650
[Door Closes,
Alarm Chirps]

30
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:39,070
What are you talking about?
These tracks are only a few days old.

31
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:42,407
Tracks?
What are you? Pocahontas?

32
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:44,409
Come on!

33
00:04:51,499 --> 00:04:53,918
Let's take a look inside.

34
00:04:54,002 --> 00:04:55,962
[Sighs]

35
00:05:12,103 --> 00:05:14,230
[Thinking]
"Teddy."

36
00:05:14,272 --> 00:05:18,443
"Don't believe his lies.
He is the one. Kill him."

37
00:05:18,484 --> 00:05:22,238
I finally found him.
How long have I been looking?

38
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:26,242
Find anything?

39
00:05:26,325 --> 00:05:28,536
Didn't think so.

40
00:05:28,619 --> 00:05:32,290
Let's go, huh?
Oh, fuck this.

41
00:05:32,373 --> 00:05:35,126
- [Teddy Grunts]
- You're gonna pay for what you did.

42
00:05:35,168 --> 00:05:38,963
Beg forgiveness,
and then you pay.

43
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:42,592
[Panting]

44
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:45,595
You don't have a clue,
you freak.

45
00:05:45,636 --> 00:05:49,474
Beg My wife's forgiveness
before I blow your brains out.

46
00:05:49,557 --> 00:05:52,518
Leonard, you don't know
what's going on.

47
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:55,104
- You don't even know my name.
- Teddy.

48
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:57,356
That's 'cause you read it
off a fucking picture.

49
00:05:57,440 --> 00:06:00,735
You don't know who you are.

50
00:06:00,818 --> 00:06:03,613
I'm Leonard Shelby.
I'm from San Francisco.

51
00:06:03,654 --> 00:06:07,325
That's who you were.
That's not what you've become.

52
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:10,161
- Shut your mouth.
- You want to know, Lenny?

53
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:13,164
Come on. Come on, let's
go down to the basement.

54
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:16,959
Let's go down,
you and me, together.

55
00:06:17,001 --> 00:06:19,420
Then you'll know
who you really are.

56
00:06:22,673 --> 00:06:24,967
- No!
- [Gunshot]

57
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:28,387
[Narrating]
it's just an anonymous room.

58
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:30,973
There's nothing in the drawers.
But you look anyway.

59
00:06:31,057 --> 00:06:35,478
Nothing except the Gideon Bible,
which I, of course, read religiously.

60
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:37,522
[Chuckles, Sighs]

61
00:06:37,563 --> 00:06:42,568
You know, you know who you are, and
you know kind of all about yourself.

62
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:47,490
But just for day-to-day stuff,,
notes are really useful.

63
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:50,535
Sammy Jankis
had the same problem,

64
00:06:50,618 --> 00:06:52,829
but he really had no system.

65
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:55,039
He wrote himself
a ridiculous amount of notes,

66
00:06:55,123 --> 00:06:57,041
but he 'he'd get them all mixed up.

67
00:06:57,125 --> 00:07:01,379
You really do need a system if--
if you're gonna make it work.

68
00:07:52,555 --> 00:07:54,891
[Bell Buzzes]

69
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:58,227
- Hi.
- Hi.

70
00:07:58,269 --> 00:08:01,564
- I'm Mr. Shel by from 304.
- What can I do for you, Leonard?

71
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:03,482
- Um--
- Burt.

72
00:08:03,566 --> 00:08:06,944
Burt. I'm not sure. I think I may have
asked you to hold my calls.

73
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:09,822
- You don't know?
- I'm not too good on the phone.

74
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:13,117
Right. You said you like to look people
in the eye when you talk to them.

75
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:15,786
- Yeah.
- You don't remember saying that?

76
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:19,123
- Well, that's the thing.
I have this condition.
- Condition?

77
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:21,626
- It's my memory.
- Amnesia?

78
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:24,754
No, no, no. It's different from that.
I have no short-term memory.

79
00:08:24,837 --> 00:08:27,506
I know who I am.
I know all about myself.

80
00:08:27,590 --> 00:08:31,385
Since my injury, I can't make
new memories. Everything fades.

81
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:34,013
If we talk for too long,
I'll forget how we started.

82
00:08:34,096 --> 00:08:37,225
The next time I see you, I'm not
gonna remember this conversation.

83
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:40,394
[Laughs] I don't even know
if I've met you before.

84
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:44,523
So if I seem a little strange
or rude or something, uh--

85
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:48,027
I've told you this
before, haven't I?

86
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:52,198
Yeah. I mean, I don't mean
to mess with you, but it's so weird.

87
00:08:52,281 --> 00:08:54,492
- You don't remember me at all?
- No.

88
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:57,453
- We've talked a bunch of times.
- I'm sure we have.

89
00:08:57,495 --> 00:09:00,539
Well, what's the last thing
you remember?

90
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:02,583
My wife.

91
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:04,794
What's it like?

92
00:09:09,632 --> 00:09:13,177
It's like waking.
It's like you just woke up.

93
00:09:14,553 --> 00:09:16,514
That must suck.

94
00:09:16,555 --> 00:09:19,183
I mean, it's all backwards.

95
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:22,436
Like, may be you get an idea about
what you want to do next,

96
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,981
but you don't remember
what You just did.

97
00:09:25,022 --> 00:09:28,609
- I'm exactly the opposite--
- How long have I been staying here?

98
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:30,903
- A couple of days.
- And you're holding my calls?

99
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:34,365
- like you said.
- Okay, but this guy's an exception.

100
00:09:34,448 --> 00:09:38,369
- Do you know this guy?
- Yeah, it's your friend, right?

101
00:09:38,411 --> 00:09:41,038
What makes you think
he's my friend?

102
00:09:41,122 --> 00:09:43,541
- I just saw you together, that's all.
- He's not my friend.

103
00:09:43,624 --> 00:09:46,168
- Okay.
- if he calls or if he shows up here,

104
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:48,838
you give me a call
in my room, okay?

105
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:51,215
- What, his name's Teddy?
- Teddy, yeah.

106
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:53,301
All right.

107
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:57,054
Look, I hope my condition's
not gonna be a problem for you.

108
00:09:57,096 --> 00:10:00,057
No, not as long as you
remember to pay the bill.

109
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:02,727
- Okay.
- Forty.

110
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:07,773
This guy--

111
00:10:07,857 --> 00:10:10,860
He's here already.

112
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:12,903
Lenny!

113
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:18,159
[Narrating] You really needa system
if you're gonna make it work.

114
00:10:18,242 --> 00:10:21,454
You kind of learn
to trust your own hand writing.

115
00:10:21,537 --> 00:10:24,415
That becomes an important part
of your life. You write your self notes.

116
00:10:24,498 --> 00:10:26,876
And where you put your notes--
That also becomes important.

117
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:30,504
You need a jacket that's got
like six pockets in it.

118
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:33,215
Particular pockets
for particular things.

119
00:10:33,257 --> 00:10:37,094
You just kind of learn to know where
things go and how the system works.

120
00:10:37,136 --> 00:10:41,932
You have to be wary of
other people writing stuff, for you,
that it's gonna lead you astray.

121
00:10:41,974 --> 00:10:46,187
I mean, I don't know how these
people try and take advantage
of somebody with this condition.

122
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:51,067
If you have a piece
of information which is vital,

123
00:10:51,108 --> 00:10:54,945
writing on your body instead of
on a piece of paper can be the answer.

124
00:10:55,029 --> 00:10:57,323
It's just a permanent way
of keeping a note.

125
00:10:57,406 --> 00:10:59,617
[Phone Ringing]

126
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:06,290
Who is this?

127
00:11:13,714 --> 00:11:15,966
[Thinking]
"Remember Sam my Jankis."

128
00:11:28,604 --> 00:11:31,023
[Door Opening]

129
00:11:39,657 --> 00:11:42,701
[Quiet Chattering]

130
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:48,457
Excuse me, sir.
You left these at your table.

131
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:51,544
Thanks. Uh... Lincoln Street?

132
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:53,754
Oh, yeah, just go
straight out on Sixth Street.

133
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:55,756
I'm gonna write this down.

134
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:59,135
- It's easy.Just go--
- Trust me. I need to write this down.

135
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:08,144
[Thinking]
"The Discount Inn."

136
00:12:26,036 --> 00:12:28,247
[Drops key]

137
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:33,878
[Thinking]
Discount Inn.

138
00:12:33,961 --> 00:12:36,714
Natalie.

139
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:41,510
My car.

140
00:12:41,552 --> 00:12:43,846
Teddy.

141
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:58,736
"John Edward Gammell."

142
00:13:00,571 --> 00:13:03,407
This guy told me
his name was Teddy.

143
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:09,288
"Don't believe his lies."

144
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:15,294
[Dial Tone]

145
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:18,255
[Dialing]

146
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:22,301
[Line Ringing]

147
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:27,723
- [Man On Phone]
Yeah? Lenny, is that you?
- Mr. Gammell?

148
00:13:27,765 --> 00:13:30,601
- John Gammell?
- Lenny, it's Teddy. Stay there.

149
00:13:30,684 --> 00:13:33,187
- I'll be right over.
- Okay. I'll be waiting.

150
00:14:32,871 --> 00:14:35,165
"White. Male"

151
00:14:35,207 --> 00:14:38,168
"First name John."

152
00:14:38,252 --> 00:14:42,131
"Last name 'G' for Gammell."

153
00:14:47,177 --> 00:14:49,847
"Drugs. License plate."

154
00:14:51,181 --> 00:14:53,350
"SG1 3...

155
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:57,313
7I U."

156
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:03,861
It's him.

157
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:12,202
I found you, you fuck.

158
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:15,933
You said we talked before.
I don't remember that.

159
00:16:16,016 --> 00:16:19,687
Yeah, but it's not amnesia. I remember
everything up until my injury.

160
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:22,898
I just can't make new memories.
So I can't remember talking to you.

161
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:25,442
What did we talk about?
Oh, Sammy Jankis.

162
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:27,778
I tell people about Sammy
to help them understand.

163
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:31,115
Sammy's story helps me
understand my own situation.

164
00:16:31,198 --> 00:16:35,828
Well, Sammy wrote himself endless
amounts of notes, but he got mixed up.

165
00:16:35,911 --> 00:16:40,332
I have a more graceful
solution to the memory problem.

166
00:16:42,626 --> 00:16:45,129
I'm disciplined and organized.

167
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:48,298
I use habit and routine
to make my life possible.

168
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:51,844
Sammy had no drive,
no reason to make it work.

169
00:16:51,927 --> 00:16:56,807
Me? Yeah, I got a reason.

170
00:17:09,445 --> 00:17:11,613
[Car Alarm Chirps]

171
00:17:14,908 --> 00:17:18,704
[Thinking] "Today, 1:00 p.m.
Meet Natalie for info.

172
00:17:18,787 --> 00:17:21,165
"She has also lost someone.

173
00:17:21,248 --> 00:17:24,293
She will help you out of pity."

174
00:17:40,476 --> 00:17:42,978
- Natalie?
- You don't remember me.

175
00:17:43,061 --> 00:17:47,024
- I'm sorry. I should have
explained. I have this--
- You did explain, Lenny.

176
00:17:47,065 --> 00:17:49,485
Please call me Leonard.
My wife called me Lenny.

177
00:17:49,526 --> 00:17:53,155
- Yeah, I know. You told me.
- Then I probably told you
how much I hated it.

178
00:17:53,197 --> 00:17:55,157
Yeah.

179
00:17:55,199 --> 00:17:59,661
Do you mind taking your glasses off?
It's hard for me to--

180
00:17:59,703 --> 00:18:03,165
Thanks. So you have
information for me?

181
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:06,043
- Is that what your little note says?
- Yeah.

182
00:18:06,084 --> 00:18:09,546
Must be tough living your life according
to a couple of scraps of paper.

183
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:13,091
Mix your laundry list with your
grocery list, and you'll end up
eating your underwear.

184
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:16,929
I guess that's why you have
those freaky tattoos.

185
00:18:17,012 --> 00:18:21,183
Yeah, it's tough.
It's almost impossible.

186
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:24,228
Look, I'm sorry I don't remember you.
It's nothing personal.

187
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:30,067
I do have information for you.

188
00:18:30,150 --> 00:18:32,945
You gave me a license plate number.

189
00:18:33,028 --> 00:18:36,240
Had my friend at D.M.V. trace it.

190
00:18:36,281 --> 00:18:39,243
Guess what name came up.

191
00:18:39,326 --> 00:18:42,579
John Edward Gammell.John G.

192
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:45,290
- Do you know him?
- No.

193
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:48,460
But his face on his driver's
license looked really familiar.

194
00:18:48,544 --> 00:18:50,546
I think he's been
in the bar, maybe.

195
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:54,216
Here's a copy of his license,
his registration, photo and all.

196
00:18:54,258 --> 00:18:56,218
are you sure you want this?

197
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:58,554
Have I told you
what this man did?

198
00:18:58,595 --> 00:19:01,431
- Yeah.
- Then you shouldn't have to ask.

199
00:19:01,515 --> 00:19:03,767
But even If you get revenge,
you're not gonna remember it.

200
00:19:03,809 --> 00:19:05,894
You're not even gonna know
that it happened.

201
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:09,314
My wife deserves vengeance.
Doesn't make any difference
whether I know about it.

202
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:14,194
Just because there are things
I don't remember doesn't make
my actions meaningless.

203
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:17,781
The world doesn't just disappear
when you close your eyes, does it?

204
00:19:17,865 --> 00:19:21,410
Anyway, maybe I'll take
a photograph to remind myself,

205
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:23,662
get another freaky tattoo.

206
00:19:27,624 --> 00:19:30,627
Tell me about her again.

207
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:32,629
Why?

208
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:35,465
Because you
like to remember her.

209
00:19:37,384 --> 00:19:41,930
She was beautiful.
To me, she was perfect.

210
00:19:41,972 --> 00:19:46,643
No. Don't
just recite the words.

211
00:19:46,727 --> 00:19:51,398
Close your eyes...
and remember her.

212
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,620
You can just feel the details.

213
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:09,374
The bits and pieces you never
bothered to put into words.

214
00:20:13,337 --> 00:20:16,882
And you can feel
these extreme moments...

215
00:20:16,965 --> 00:20:18,884
even If you don't want to.

216
00:20:21,553 --> 00:20:24,556
You put these together, and
you get the feel ofa person.

217
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:31,063
Enough to know
how much you miss them...

218
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:38,570
and how much you hate
the person who took them away.

219
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:51,583
I, um-- I added
an address in here.

220
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:55,170
It might be useful. It's an abandoned
place outside of town.

221
00:20:55,212 --> 00:20:58,173
A guy I knew used to do
bigger deals there.

222
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:02,260
It's isolated.

223
00:21:02,344 --> 00:21:04,262
Sounds perfect.

224
00:21:06,306 --> 00:21:08,225
Do I owe you any--

225
00:21:08,308 --> 00:21:10,227
I wasn't helping you for money.

226
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:12,562
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

227
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:16,692
"See, you have this condition."
[Laughs]

228
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:20,696
Oh, are you still staying
at the Discount Inn, room 304?
You left it at my place.

229
00:21:26,284 --> 00:21:29,579
Yeah.
[Chuckles]

230
00:21:29,621 --> 00:21:32,416
- They treating you okay?
- I don't remember.

231
00:21:32,457 --> 00:21:37,295
[Laughs]
You know what we have in common?

232
00:21:39,297 --> 00:21:43,093
We are both survivors.

233
00:21:43,176 --> 00:21:46,680
You take care, Leonard.

234
00:21:53,895 --> 00:21:57,899
[Door Opens, Closes]

235
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:17,669
[Thinking]
"Remember Sammy Jankis."

