Wait a minute.

497
00:42:11,987 --> 00:42:15,032
- Is that John G.?
- I don't think so.

498
00:42:15,115 --> 00:42:18,619
- You don't think so?
You didn't write it down?
- I might've fallen asleep.

499
00:42:18,702 --> 00:42:21,580
For Christ's sakes!

500
00:42:21,664 --> 00:42:23,958
Ask him.

501
00:42:26,543 --> 00:42:30,047
- What's your name? Your name!
- [Mutters]

502
00:42:30,130 --> 00:42:32,508
- Dodd.
- And who did this to you?

503
00:42:32,549 --> 00:42:35,135
- What?
- Who did this to you?

504
00:42:35,219 --> 00:42:37,304
You did.

505
00:42:39,556 --> 00:42:42,142
Look, I'm not gonna
help you kill that guy.

506
00:42:42,226 --> 00:42:44,520
No, just let me
think for a minute.

507
00:42:46,397 --> 00:42:48,983
[Muffled Crying Continues]

508
00:42:49,024 --> 00:42:51,652
- Okay, Natalie.
- who's Natalie?

509
00:42:51,694 --> 00:42:53,654
- Natalie who?
- Why?

510
00:42:53,696 --> 00:42:56,782
Maybe I know her. Look, we gotta
get him out of here.

511
00:42:56,865 --> 00:42:59,618
All right, all right,
all right, all right.

512
00:42:59,702 --> 00:43:01,787
He's gotta have
a car, right?

513
00:43:01,870 --> 00:43:05,624
So we take him down to his car,
we tell him to get out of town
or we're gonna kill him.

514
00:43:05,708 --> 00:43:08,127
We can't just walk him
out of here tied up and bleeding.

515
00:43:08,210 --> 00:43:10,629
- How the fuck
did you get him up here?
- I don't know!

516
00:43:10,713 --> 00:43:12,631
You don't know.

517
00:43:14,216 --> 00:43:16,343
Yes, I do.
This is not my room.

518
00:43:16,385 --> 00:43:18,887
- It must be his room. Great! Let's go.
- No, no, no.

519
00:43:18,971 --> 00:43:21,181
- We can't just leave him here.
- Why not?

520
00:43:21,223 --> 00:43:25,352
The maid's gonna walk in.
She'll see him, call the cops.
He can I.D. us.

521
00:43:26,770 --> 00:43:29,356
Okay. We untie him,
we clean him up...

522
00:43:29,398 --> 00:43:32,026
and we march him out of here
with a gun in his back.

523
00:43:32,067 --> 00:43:34,903
A gun.
Why would I have a gun?

524
00:43:34,945 --> 00:43:39,241
- It must be his.
- I don't think they'd let
someone like me carry a gun.

525
00:43:39,283 --> 00:43:41,243
Fucking hope not.

526
00:43:48,584 --> 00:43:50,502
Which one?

527
00:43:53,088 --> 00:43:56,008
We should probably steal his car.
You know, teach him a lesson.

528
00:43:56,091 --> 00:43:59,053
- Shut up.
- That's all right for you to say.
You're the one with the Jag.

529
00:43:59,094 --> 00:44:02,139
All right, get in.
I'm gonna ride with him.
You follow us.

530
00:44:02,222 --> 00:44:04,141
Give me your keys.

531
00:44:04,224 --> 00:44:06,435
Take your own car.

532
00:44:09,730 --> 00:44:11,982
[Engine Starts]

533
00:44:21,825 --> 00:44:24,661
[Tires Squealing]

534
00:44:34,004 --> 00:44:37,466
- So was he scared?
- Yeah. I think it was
your sinister moustache.

535
00:44:37,508 --> 00:44:41,428
Fuck you. You should have
stolen his car.

536
00:44:41,470 --> 00:44:43,847
- What's wrong with this one?
- Nothing. You want to trade?

537
00:44:43,931 --> 00:44:46,600
[Sighs]

538
00:44:46,683 --> 00:44:48,769
So what Do you do now?

539
00:44:48,811 --> 00:44:52,106
I'm going to find out what
the fuck that was all about.

540
00:44:55,442 --> 00:44:58,153
[Knocking]

541
00:44:58,237 --> 00:45:01,323
Natalie, right?
Who the fuck is Dodd?

542
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:06,995
Sammy's wife was crippled
by the cost of supporting him...

543
00:45:07,079 --> 00:45:09,998
and fighting
the company's decision.

544
00:45:10,082 --> 00:45:13,335
But it wasn't the money
that got to her.

545
00:45:13,419 --> 00:45:16,463
- I never said
that Sammy was faking.
- Listen. I have an idea.

546
00:45:16,505 --> 00:45:19,007
Sammy, I have an idea
I want you to do for me.

547
00:45:19,091 --> 00:45:21,927
Just that his problem
was mental, not physical.

548
00:45:22,010 --> 00:45:24,721
I want you to have
a pen in your pocket, okay?

549
00:45:24,805 --> 00:45:27,141
- You're gonna have
a pen in your pocket.
- She couldn't understand.

550
00:45:27,182 --> 00:45:30,519
- I did something wrong.
- You did something wrong!
We're gonna deal with it.

551
00:45:30,602 --> 00:45:34,356
- We're gonna try harder--
- when she looks into his eyes
and sees the same person.

552
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:38,068
- You can't go anywhere!
- if It's not a physical problem,
he should just snap out ofit.

553
00:45:38,152 --> 00:45:40,487
- Ellen called! [Crying]
- Ellen called?

554
00:45:40,529 --> 00:45:44,074
- Ellen can't come today!
Ellen can't come!
- Okay. I'm sorry!

555
00:45:44,158 --> 00:45:47,286
- I'm sorry. I'm trying. I'm sorry.
- Try harder!

556
00:45:50,289 --> 00:45:55,169
So good old Leonard Shelby
from the insurance company
gives her the seed of doubt...

557
00:45:55,210 --> 00:45:57,838
just like he gave it
to the doctors.

558
00:45:57,921 --> 00:46:02,009
But I never said that he was faking.
I never said that.

559
00:46:07,222 --> 00:46:10,100
[Thinking]
Hmm, I don't feel drunk.

560
00:46:44,051 --> 00:46:46,428
[Door Closes]

561
00:46:46,470 --> 00:46:48,472
[Clattering]

562
00:46:48,555 --> 00:46:51,058
[Urinating]

563
00:46:53,352 --> 00:46:56,063
[Toilet Flushing]

564
00:47:00,817 --> 00:47:05,405
[Both Grunting]

565
00:47:22,297 --> 00:47:25,300
- [woman knocking]
Hello? Housekeeping.
- Oh, shit.

566
00:47:25,384 --> 00:47:28,095
- Not right now.
- Oh, I'm sorry.

567
00:47:50,784 --> 00:47:52,703
Okay.

568
00:47:55,914 --> 00:47:58,542
[Thinking]
"Dodd. Put him onto Teddy...

569
00:47:58,625 --> 00:48:01,003
or just get rid of him
for Natalie."

570
00:48:05,757 --> 00:48:07,676
Dodd.

571
00:48:12,848 --> 00:48:15,183
Get rid of him.

572
00:48:15,225 --> 00:48:17,853
Ask Natalie.

573
00:48:17,936 --> 00:48:20,731
Teddy, Teddy.

574
00:48:20,814 --> 00:48:23,609
[Dial Tone]

575
00:48:25,527 --> 00:48:27,904
[Line Ringing]

576
00:48:30,490 --> 00:48:33,410
[Teddy's voice On Machine]
Yeah, leave your number.
You know what to do.

577
00:48:33,493 --> 00:48:35,829
Yeah. This is a message
for Teddy.

578
00:48:35,871 --> 00:48:38,373
I'm at the Mount crest Inn
of Fifth Street, room six.

579
00:48:38,457 --> 00:48:41,293
I need you to come over
as soon as you get this.
It's important.

580
00:48:41,376 --> 00:48:44,212
Oh, this is Leonard.
Thanks. Bye.

581
00:48:45,380 --> 00:48:48,467
Whew. Fuck.

582
00:48:51,219 --> 00:48:54,014
[Sighing]

583
00:48:58,393 --> 00:49:02,064
Mrs.Jankis didn't understand
that you can't bully someone
into remembering.

584
00:49:02,147 --> 00:49:05,067
The more pressure you're under,
the harder it gets.

585
00:49:05,108 --> 00:49:08,445
Uh, well, then call me--
call me back?

586
00:49:25,212 --> 00:49:29,216
[Car Alarm Blaring]

587
00:49:30,926 --> 00:49:33,637
[Thinking]
Okay, so what am I doing?

588
00:49:34,971 --> 00:49:37,432
Oh, I'm chasing this guy.

589
00:49:39,226 --> 00:49:41,895
No. He's chasing me.

590
00:49:45,482 --> 00:49:48,568
[Alarm Continues Blaring]

591
00:49:49,986 --> 00:49:53,573
[Alarm Chirps, Stops]

592
00:49:53,657 --> 00:49:55,826
[Engine Starts]

593
00:49:58,245 --> 00:50:00,580
[Tires Screeching]

594
00:50:02,916 --> 00:50:06,294
[Groaning]
Fuck.

595
00:50:09,715 --> 00:50:12,008
[Thinking]
"Dodd. White guy.

596
00:50:12,092 --> 00:50:14,970
Mount crest I nn
on Fifth Street."

597
00:50:15,011 --> 00:50:17,931
I'll get the jump on you,
you fucker.

598
00:50:48,503 --> 00:50:50,630
[Man On Television]
$9995, $98 a month.

599
00:50:50,714 --> 00:50:54,718
A '97 Toyota RAV-4,
$11,995, $110 a month.

600
00:50:54,801 --> 00:50:58,555
- Oh, fuck.
- A '96 Dodge Caravan,
$8995, $95 a month.

601
00:50:58,638 --> 00:51:00,682
- Sorry.
- A '97--

602
00:51:33,215 --> 00:51:35,175
[Thinking]
I need a weapon.

603
00:51:38,470 --> 00:51:40,639
This will do.

604
00:52:02,369 --> 00:52:05,789
Hmm, I don't feel drunk.

605
00:52:36,111 --> 00:52:38,905
[Car Alarm Chirps]

606
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:44,995
[Horn Honking]

607
00:52:47,330 --> 00:52:49,457
[Thinking]
Do I know this guy?

608
00:52:49,541 --> 00:52:52,460
- [Honking Continues]
- He seems to know me.

609
00:52:57,299 --> 00:52:59,342
What the fuck?

610
00:53:12,022 --> 00:53:14,482
- I like your car.
- Thank you.

611
00:53:14,566 --> 00:53:16,610
- Where'd you get it?
- Are you interested in buying one?

612
00:53:16,651 --> 00:53:19,154
What, I haven't made a strong enough
impression on you?

613
00:53:19,195 --> 00:53:21,865
I wouldn't be
too hard on yourself.

614
00:53:31,917 --> 00:53:34,961
[Thinking]
Okay, so what am I doing?

615
00:53:42,469 --> 00:53:45,680
- [Phone Ringing]
- Who is this?

616
00:53:50,352 --> 00:53:52,812
[Car Alarm Chirps]

617
00:54:29,516 --> 00:54:31,935
[Car Alarm Chirps]

618
00:55:04,843 --> 00:55:06,761
Ouch. Cut it out.

619
00:55:38,543 --> 00:55:41,755
- How can you read that again?
- It's good.

620
00:55:41,796 --> 00:55:44,841
Yeah, but you've read it,
like, a thousand times.

621
00:55:44,924 --> 00:55:46,509
I enjoy it.

622
00:55:46,593 --> 00:55:49,429
I always thought
the pleasure of a book...

623
00:55:49,471 --> 00:55:52,307
- was in wanting to know
what happens next.
- Look, don't be a prick.

624
00:55:52,390 --> 00:55:56,019
I'm not reading it
to annoy you. I enjoy it.

625
00:55:56,102 --> 00:55:59,272
J Just let me read, please.

626
00:56:09,449 --> 00:56:11,826
[Thinking]
Probably tried this before.

627
00:56:13,953 --> 00:56:17,957
Probably burned truckloads
of your stuff.

628
00:56:17,999 --> 00:56:21,336
Can't remember
to forget you.

629
00:56:39,813 --> 00:56:42,982
Yeah. Uh-huh.

630
00:56:43,024 --> 00:56:47,987
Well, sir, that'd certainly be
in keeping with some of
my own discoveries.

631
00:56:48,071 --> 00:56:51,491
I was hoping for a little more
on the drugs angle. Hang on a sec?

632
00:56:59,541 --> 00:57:03,336
Now, the police report mentioned
the drugs found in the car
outside my house.

633
00:57:03,378 --> 00:57:05,505
The carwas stolen.
Bloody prints were all over it.

634
00:57:05,547 --> 00:57:08,258
I got friends in the department.
They gave me a copy ofit.

635
00:57:08,341 --> 00:57:11,386
I dealt with the police a lot
in my insurance job.

636
00:57:11,469 --> 00:57:15,348
With my condition, it's really tough.
I can't keep it all in mind at once.

637
00:57:15,390 --> 00:57:18,184
I have to summarize
the different sections.
And there's pages missing.

638
00:57:18,226 --> 00:57:20,395
I guess I've been trying
to log them all.

639
00:57:20,478 --> 00:57:22,730
I don't know why
these are crossed out.

640
00:57:22,814 --> 00:57:24,732
But they weren't even
looking for John G.

641
00:57:24,816 --> 00:57:27,152
The stuff they found in the car
just fit in with what they
believed had happened,

642
00:57:27,235 --> 00:57:30,446
so they didn't chase
any ofit up.

643
00:57:30,530 --> 00:57:32,907
[Door Squeaks, Shuts]

644
00:58:05,815 --> 00:58:07,984
Honey.

645
00:58:08,067 --> 00:58:10,862
Honey, it's late.

646
00:58:33,301 --> 00:58:35,261
Everything okay?

647
00:58:51,569 --> 00:58:54,113
- [Muffled Cries]
- You okay in there?

648
00:58:57,617 --> 00:58:59,535
Was it good for you?

649
00:59:01,746 --> 00:59:04,666
What? Was I supposed
to lock the door?

650
00:59:04,707 --> 00:59:06,668
No.

651
00:59:09,087 --> 00:59:11,005
I'd like you to leave now.

652
00:59:21,808 --> 00:59:24,811
[Car Alarm Chirps]

653
00:59:31,192 --> 00:59:35,071
There's something about
the drugs stashed in the car
that doesn't ring true for me.

654
00:59:35,154 --> 00:59:37,156
Because the police claim
the guy was an addict,

655
00:59:37,198 --> 00:59:39,659
needing money to score,
which I think is bullshit,

656
00:59:39,701 --> 00:59:43,997
'cause he's not gonna go
breaking into places while
he's still got a stash that big.

657
00:59:44,038 --> 00:59:46,666
Well, I think John G. left it there
or planted it there.

658
00:59:48,543 --> 00:59:50,545
How Do you know that?

659
00:59:50,628 --> 00:59:54,674
Oh, shit, that's true. It fits.

660
00:59:54,716 --> 00:59:57,260
So he's a dealer.

661
00:59:57,343 --> 00:59:59,262
Hang on a sec.

662
01:00:08,688 --> 01:00:11,399
Now we're getting somewhere.

663
01:00:11,482 --> 01:00:13,026
"Discount Inn."

664
01:00:17,655 --> 01:00:19,574
[Alarm Chirps]

665
01:01:05,787 --> 01:01:07,789
Yeah, okay.

666
01:01:07,872 --> 01:01:10,500
Blonde's fine.

667
01:01:10,583 --> 01:01:12,794
[Chuckles]
Well, that's what they say.

668
01:01:12,877 --> 01:01:15,922
The Discount Inn. 304.

669
01:01:16,005 --> 01:01:17,965
Leonard.

670
01:01:19,425 --> 01:01:20,843
Well, what then?

671
01:01:20,927 --> 01:01:24,305
We just go to bed.
You wait for me to fall asleep.

672
01:01:24,389 --> 01:01:26,307
You go into the bathroom
and you slam the door.

673
01:01:26,391 --> 01:01:28,935
- Slam it?
- Yeah. Loud enough
to wake me up.

674
01:01:29,018 --> 01:01:30,978
- And that's it?
- That's it.

675
01:01:31,020 --> 01:01:33,689
Uh,

676
01:01:33,773 --> 01:01:36,776
yeah, first I just need you to put
these things around the room.

677
01:01:39,862 --> 01:01:42,990
Just pretend they're your things
and that this is your bedroom.

678
01:01:54,794 --> 01:01:59,674
- Should I wear it?
- No, no, no. Uh, just like
you took it off or something.

679
01:02:02,635 --> 01:02:05,054
I-I don't want you
to use it. I'm sorry.

680
01:02:05,138 --> 01:02:08,850
Just-- I just mean put them
around the room, you know,

681
01:02:08,933 --> 01:02:12,395
as if they were
your-- your things.

682
01:02:15,231 --> 01:02:17,984
Whatever gets you off.

683
01:02:36,878 --> 01:02:39,505
[Door Squeaks, Shuts]

684
01:02:41,716 --> 01:02:46,679
I can't blame the cops
for not taking me seriously.
This is difficult to understand.

685
01:02:46,721 --> 01:02:50,475
I mean, look at Sammy Jankis.
His own wife couldn't deal with it.

686
01:02:50,558 --> 01:02:52,894
I told you about how she tried
to get him to snap out ofit.

687
01:02:52,935 --> 01:02:55,730
Eventually she came
to see me at the office.
I found out all kinds of shit.

688
01:02:55,813 --> 01:03:00,860
- She told me about life with
Sammy, how she treated him.
- Thank you for seeing me.

689
01:03:00,943 --> 01:03:03,696
It got to the point where
she'd get Sammy to hide food
all around the house...

690
01:03:03,738 --> 01:03:06,532
and then she'd stop feeding him
just to see if his hunger...

691
01:03:06,574 --> 01:03:09,660
would make him remember
where he'd hidden the food.

692
01:03:09,744 --> 01:03:12,580
She wasn't a cruel person.
She just wanted old Sammy back.

693
01:03:12,622 --> 01:03:16,417
Mr. Shelby, you know all about Sammy
and you've decided that he's faking.

694
01:03:16,501 --> 01:03:19,170
Mrs.Jankis, the company's position
isn't that Sammy is faking anything.

695
01:03:19,253 --> 01:03:21,631
It's just that his condition
can't be shown to be--

696
01:03:21,714 --> 01:03:24,717
I just wanna know what your
honest opinion about Sammy is.

697
01:03:24,759 --> 01:03:27,720
We shouldn't even be talking like this
while the case is still open to appeal.

698
01:03:27,762 --> 01:03:31,015
- I'm not appealing the decision.
- Then why are you here?

699
